{"lemma":"بَياناتٌ","slug":"بَياناتٌ","root":"ب.#.ن","root_slug":"ب-_-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-_-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"بَيان","root":"بين","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":15},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3671"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%8A%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَانَ (bāna) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"clearness, obviousness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"statement"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"declaration, announcement"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"explanation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"commentary"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"evident meaning"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"demonstration"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"eloquence, rhetoric"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"division"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"exposé"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"official report"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"communiqué"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"list"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"piano"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ba.jaːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3671","headword_ar":"بَيَانٌ","root":"byn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is originally the inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAna","text_ar":"بَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabay~ana","text_ar":"تَبَيَّنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and so signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distinct"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apparent"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; (Kull;) or it is a subst. in this sense: (Msb:) or a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bay~ana","text_ar":"بَيَّنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [and so signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making distinct"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apparent"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,] being like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAmN","text_ar":"سَلَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalaAmN","text_ar":"كَلَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sal~ama","text_ar":"سَلَّمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kal~ama","text_ar":"كَلَّمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Kull.) ―         -b2-  Hence, conventionally, (Kull,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"means by which one makes"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distinct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apparent, manifest, evident, clear, plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perspicuous:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Er-Rághib, TA, Kull:) this is of two kinds: one is ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a circumstantial indication"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evidence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing indicating,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"giving evidence of, a circumstance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state, that is a result,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an effect, of a quality"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an attribute:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the other is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a verbal indication"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evidence, either spoken or written:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bay~inapN","text_ar":"بَيِّنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] it is also applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"language that discovers and shows the meaning that is intended:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an explanation of confused and vague language:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eduction"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from a state of dubiousness to a state of clearness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making the meaning apparent to the mind so that it becomes distinct from other meanings and from what might be confounded with it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Perspicuity, clearness, distinctness, chasteness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eloquence, of speech"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"language:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S:) or simply"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perspicuity thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 2:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perspicuity of speech with quickness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharpness, of intellect:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perspicuous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chaste,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eloquent, speech, declaring,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"telling plainly, what is in the mind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ksh, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"showing of the intent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meaning, with the most eloquent expression:"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is an effect of understanding, and of sharpness, or quickness, of mind, with perspicuity, or chasteness, or eloquence, of speech: (Nh, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a faculty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"principles,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or a science,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whereby one knows how to express"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with perspicuity of diction"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one meaning in various forms:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull:) [some of the Arabs restrict the science of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbyAn","text_ar":"البيان"},{"kind":"text","text":"to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what concerns comparisons and tropes and metonymies;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which last the Arabian rhetoricians distinguish from tropes: and some make it to include"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rhetoric"},{"kind":"text","text":"altogether:] Esh-Shereeshee says, in his Expos. of the Maká- mát [of El-Hareeree] that the difference between"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayaAnN","text_ar":"بَيَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiboyaAnN","text_ar":"تِبْيَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is this: that the former denotes"},{"kind":"page_break","n":289},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perspicuity of meaning;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making the meaning to be understood;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the former is to another person, and the latter to oneself; but sometimes the latter is used in the sense of the former: (TA:) or the former is the act of the tongue, and the latter is the act of the mind: (Har p. 2:) or the former concerns the verbal expression, and the latter concerns the meaning. (Kull.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a mina AlbayaAni siHorFA","text_ar":"اـِنَّ مِنَ البَيَانِ سِحْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lasiHorFA","text_ar":"لَسِحْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily there is a kind of eloquence that is enchantment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see this explained in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sHr","text_ar":"سحر"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. The saying in the Kur [lv. 2 and 3],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqa A@loA_inosaAna Eal~amahu A@lobayaAna","text_ar":"خَلَقَ ا@لْاـِنْسَانَ عَلَّمَهُ ا@لْبَيَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hath created the Prophet: He hath taught him the Kur-án wherein is the manifestation of everything"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"needful to be known"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hath created Adam,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"man"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning all mankind:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hath"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taught him speech, and so"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made him to discriminate, and thus to be distinguished from all"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"animals:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hath taught him that whereby he is distinguished from other animals,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the declaration of what is in the mind, and the making others to understand what he has perceived,"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the reception of inspiration, and the becoming acquainted with the truth, and the learning of the law. (Bd.) ―         -b4-  It is also applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verbosity, and the going deep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being extravagant, in speech, and affecting to be perspicuous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chaste, therein,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eloquent, and pretending to excel others therein;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or some"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byAn","text_ar":"بيان"},{"kind":"text","text":"is thus termed; and is blamed in a trad., as a kind of hypocrisy; as though it were a sort of self-conceit and pride. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","Kull","T","S","M","K","Ksh","TA","Nh","Zj"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}